&gt;&gt; HEY, CHECK IT OUT!

00:06:13.931 --> 00:06:16.033
THE HEADLESS RIDER!

00:06:18.769 --> 00:06:22.806
[sirens]

00:06:28.144 --> 00:06:29.878
&gt;&gt; AND THIS IS THE DAILY LIFE

00:06:29.878 --> 00:06:32.881
OF CELTY STURLUSON.

00:06:32.881 --> 00:06:34.782
AND THIS IS JUST ANOTHER DAY

00:06:34.782 --> 00:06:35.350
FOR HER.

00:06:35.350 --> 00:06:40.121
[sirens]

00:07:00.271 --> 00:07:02.340
WHEN MOST PEOPLE FIND THEMSELVES

00:07:02.340 --> 00:07:03.274
SURROUNDED BY THE

00:07:03.274 --> 00:07:05.142
EXTRAORDINARY, THEY PANIC.

00:07:05.142 --> 00:07:06.910
AND THAT’S WHEN SHE USUALLY

00:07:06.910 --> 00:07:07.811
ESCAPES.

00:07:07.811 --> 00:07:09.779
THIS IS HOW CELTY STURLUSON

00:07:09.779 --> 00:07:11.181
TYPICALLY DID THINGS.

00:07:11.181 --> 00:07:14.350
HOWEVER...

00:07:14.350 --> 00:07:16.786
&gt;&gt; I DON’T KNOW WHY, BUT WHEN

00:07:16.786 --> 00:07:17.987
THINGS LIKE YOU SHOW UP IN

00:07:17.987 --> 00:07:19.521
MOVIES OR MANGA, IT’S ALWAYS

00:07:19.521 --> 00:07:20.956
WHEN THE COPS HAVE BEEN DUPED

00:07:20.956 --> 00:07:22.157
AND ARE ON THE ROPES.

00:07:22.157 --> 00:07:23.992
AND BY THE TIME THE HERO WITH

00:07:23.992 --> 00:07:25.860
THE SUPERPOWER SHOWS UP, WE’RE

00:07:25.860 --> 00:07:27.462
GENERALLY QUIVERING IN A PUDDLE

00:07:27.462 --> 00:07:28.863
OF BLOOD TO ILLUSTRATE THE

00:07:28.863 --> 00:07:31.899
STRENGTH OF OUR OPPONENT.

00:07:31.899 --> 00:07:33.500
AND THAT’S JUST FINE.

00:07:33.500 --> 00:07:35.134
IT SIMPLY MEANS PEOPLE THINK

00:07:35.134 --> 00:07:36.536
WE’RE POWERFUL AND CAN’T BE

00:07:36.536 --> 00:07:37.971
KILLED SO EASILY.

00:07:37.971 --> 00:07:39.172
AND YOU KNOW, FOR A MOVIE,

00:07:39.172 --> 00:07:40.273
THAT WORKS.

00:07:40.273 --> 00:07:41.974
BUT I’VE ALWAYS WANTED TO ADD

00:07:41.974 --> 00:07:43.308
SOMETHING AT THAT POINT.

00:07:43.308 --> 00:07:45.110
IF BY CHANCE A MONSTER

00:07:45.110 --> 00:07:47.912
OR AN ANDROID OR EVEN A NINJA

00:07:47.912 --> 00:07:51.282
DID APPEAR, WELL, THEN,

00:07:51.282 --> 00:07:53.384
THERE’S JUST ONE THING THAT

00:07:53.384 --> 00:07:54.918
I’D WANNA SAY.

00:07:54.918 --> 00:07:56.887
[engines revving]

00:07:56.887 --> 00:07:58.555
DON’T JACK WITH THE COPS,

00:07:58.555 --> 00:07:59.956
MONSTER.

00:07:59.956 --> 00:08:02.925
[sirens]

00:08:02.925 --> 00:08:04.994
I’LL SAY IT AGAIN.

00:08:04.994 --> 00:08:07.596
STUPID MONSTER, DON’T JACK WITH

00:08:07.596 --> 00:08:08.563
THE COPS!

00:08:08.563 --> 00:08:11.800
[engines revving]

00:08:17.004 --> 00:08:18.572
&gt;&gt; [laughs]

00:08:18.572 --> 00:08:20.507
[door opens]

00:08:20.507 --> 00:08:23.243
CELTY! WELCOME--

00:08:23.243 --> 00:08:24.444
[grunts]

00:08:24.444 --> 00:08:26.479
HEY, WHAT’S WRONG?

00:08:26.479 --> 00:08:28.214
BELIEVE ME WHEN I TELL YOU

00:08:28.214 --> 00:08:30.116
THAT I AM PROUD AS A PEACOCK

00:08:30.116 --> 00:08:31.417
WHEN YOU HOLD ME LIKE THIS.

00:08:31.417 --> 00:08:33.852
WELL, MAYBE THAT ISN’T THE RIGHT

00:08:33.852 --> 00:08:36.154
EXPRESSION.

00:08:36.154 --> 00:08:38.423
HEY, WHY ARE YOU SHAKING?

00:08:38.423 --> 00:08:40.458
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?

00:08:40.458 --> 00:08:44.194
CELTY.

00:08:44.194 --> 00:08:46.196
&gt;&gt; I WAS SO SCARED!

00:08:46.196 --> 00:08:48.097
YOU HAVE NO IDEA, SHINRA!

00:08:48.097 --> 00:08:49.633
THE COPS THESE DAYS ARE

00:08:49.633 --> 00:08:50.533
BARBARIC!

00:08:50.533 --> 00:08:51.567
&gt;&gt; THE COPS?

00:08:51.567 --> 00:08:53.236
&gt;&gt; THERE WERE AT LEAST A DOZEN

00:08:53.236 --> 00:08:54.537
COP CARS AND MOTORCYCLES

00:08:54.537 --> 00:08:55.471
CHASING ME.

00:08:55.471 --> 00:08:56.605
THEY WERE LIKE ONE, BIG, SAVAGE

00:08:56.605 --> 00:08:59.007
MONSTER!

00:09:14.020 --> 00:09:16.055
&gt;&gt; [sinister laughter]

00:09:16.055 --> 00:09:17.256
&gt;&gt; [whimpers]

00:09:17.256 --> 00:09:18.323
&gt;&gt; OH, THAT’S RIGHT.

00:09:18.323 --> 00:09:19.458
THEY BROUGHT ON A NEW COP

00:09:19.458 --> 00:09:20.292
FOR YOU.

00:09:20.292 --> 00:09:21.293
I HEARD HE’S SOME HARD-ASS FROM

00:09:21.293 --> 00:09:22.327
ANOTHER DISTRICT.

00:09:22.327 --> 00:09:25.163
HE’S, UH, KINNOSUKE KUZUHARA.

00:09:25.163 --> 00:09:26.397
I’VE HEARD HE’S KNOWN FOR

00:09:26.397 --> 00:09:27.665
STARTING HIGH-SPEED CHASES

00:09:27.665 --> 00:09:29.567
THAT END IN ACCIDENTS.

00:09:29.567 --> 00:09:30.601
&gt;&gt; I WAS SCARED.

00:09:30.601 --> 00:09:32.503
I WAS REALLY SCARED.

00:09:32.503 --> 00:09:34.071
I WAS TOO FULL OF MYSELF.

00:09:34.071 --> 00:09:35.372
IF YOU FORGIVE ME, I PROMISE

00:09:35.372 --> 00:09:36.939
TO BE QUIET FROM NOW ON.

00:09:36.939 --> 00:09:38.641
I’M SORRY! I’M SORRY!

00:09:38.641 --> 00:09:39.609
I AM SO SORRY!

00:09:39.609 --> 00:09:41.577
&gt;&gt; WHO’RE YOU APOLOGIZING TO?

00:09:41.577 --> 00:09:43.579
IT’S NOT LIKE YOU TO PANIC OR

00:09:43.579 --> 00:09:45.581
ACT FRAGILE ABOUT ANYTHING.

00:09:45.581 --> 00:09:47.583
BUT WHEN WE’RE IN BED, YOU CAN

00:09:47.583 --> 00:09:49.284
SHOW THAT FRAGILE SIDE--UHH!

00:09:49.284 --> 00:09:50.618
&gt;&gt; THIS IS NOT THE TIME FOR

00:09:50.618 --> 00:09:52.987
THOSE KINDS OF COMMENTS.

00:09:52.987 --> 00:09:55.555
&gt;&gt; YEP. THAT’S MY GIRL.

00:09:55.555 --> 00:09:57.924
OKAY, CHANGING SUBJECTS.

00:09:57.924 --> 00:09:59.092
I KNOW THIS ISN’T THE BEST

00:09:59.092 --> 00:10:01.427
TIMING, BUT WOULD YOU MIND

00:10:01.427 --> 00:10:04.230
PICKING SOMEONE UP FOR ME?

00:10:04.230 --> 00:10:08.434
NO, THIS ISN’T A JOB.

00:10:08.434 --> 00:10:10.135
[sighs]

00:10:10.135 --> 00:10:11.703
HE’S BACK AGAIN.

00:10:11.703 --> 00:10:14.272
MY DAD.

00:10:14.272 --> 00:10:16.608
&gt;&gt; JEEZ, WHY CAN’T HE JUST

00:10:16.608 --> 00:10:19.510
TAKE A TAXI LIKE EVERYONE ELSE?

00:10:19.510 --> 00:10:21.144
THAT MAN HAS BEEN MESSING WITH

00:10:21.144 --> 00:10:23.179
ME SINCE THE DAY WE MET.

00:10:29.419 --> 00:10:31.687
&gt;&gt; YO, YO, SPEAK ALREADY.

00:10:31.687 --> 00:10:32.554
&gt;&gt; [masked breathing]

00:10:32.554 --> 00:10:33.422
&gt;&gt; WHAT’S WITH THIS GUY?

00:10:33.422 --> 00:10:34.389
&gt;&gt; WHAT’S WITH ALL THE WHITE?

00:10:34.389 --> 00:10:35.357
&gt;&gt; YOU’RE TOO WHITE, GRAMPS!

00:10:35.357 --> 00:10:36.224
&gt;&gt; IS THAT--?

00:10:36.224 --> 00:10:38.459
&gt;&gt; WHAT’S WRONG, OLD MAN?

00:10:38.459 --> 00:10:39.460
&gt;&gt; LOOK WHAT HE’S WEARIN’,

00:10:39.460 --> 00:10:40.028
HORADA.

00:10:40.028 --> 00:10:41.095
THE GEEZER’S MENTAL.

00:10:41.095 --> 00:10:41.962
&gt;&gt; [laughs]

00:10:41.962 --> 00:10:43.497
&gt;&gt; NOW LISTEN HERE, YOUNGSTERS.

00:10:43.497 --> 00:10:45.132
WOULDN’T YOU AGREE THAT THE AIR

